05197,"age":31,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Dawney was born in 1424, in Cowick, Yorkshire, England, his father, John Dawney, was 26 and his mother, MARGARET Joan Lound, was 24. He had at least 1 son with Lady Agnes Radcliffe. He died on 30 October 1493, in his hometown, at the age of 69, and was buried in Snaith, Yorkshire East Riding, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1424–30 Oct 1493":"1424–30. oktoober 1493","1424–1493":"1424–1493","1425–1475":"1425–1475","1427–1493":"1427–1493","1453–1522":"1453–1522","1398–1425":"1398–1425","1400–1454":"1400–1454","12 Jul 1425":"12. juuli 1425","1493":"1493","12 May 1454":"12. mai 1454","ABT 1414":"umbes 1414","20 Oct 1493":"20. oktoober 1493","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1522":"1522","30 Oct 1493":"30. oktoober 1493","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1454":"1454","1453":"1453","1398":"1398","1475":"1475","1427":"1427","Kirkley, Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Cowick, Yorkshire, England":"Cowick, Yorkshire, England","Snaith, East Riding of Yorkshire Unitary Authority, East Riding of Yorkshire, England":"Snaith, Yorkshire East Riding, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1424–30 Oct 1493":"1424–30. lokakuuta 1493","1424–1493":"1424–1493","1425–1475":"1425–1475","1427–1493":"1427–1493","1453–1522":"1453–1522","1398–1425":"1398–1425","1400–1454":"1400–1454","12 Jul 1425":"12. heinäkuuta 1425","1493":"1493","12 May 1454":"12. toukokuuta 1454","ABT 1414":"noin 1414","2